observationText: The SK-MEL-406 cell line was used as a target cell line in cytotoxicity assays with cytotoxic T lymphocyte (CTL) clones, indicating it is a melanoma cell line.
The SK-MEL-406 cell line was shown to express the melanoma cell surface antigens M-2, M-5, HLA-DR, M-4, M-7, M-9, and M-10 in an immunohistochemical analysis.
The SK-MEL-406 cell line was found to have a heterozygous BRAF V600E mutation.
